of these questions and answered them below.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-274_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-275_"><div class="sc-dcJtft hisXnU pf-276_ pf-icon-right" data-scrolling="false" data-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion"><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-277_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-278_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="a4b13a65-8800-4fcc-87b8-f323ad6143bd" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What are the 4 main functions of the spine?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="a4b13a65-8800-4fcc-87b8-f323ad6143bd" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-280_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-281_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-283_">It connects different parts of your musculoskeletal system. Your spine helps you sit, stand, walk, twist and bend. Back injuries, spinal cord conditions and other problems can damage the spine and cause back pain.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-284_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-285_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="0bf4ef8f-8061-49e1-a885-80a498157b48" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What part of the spine controls the legs?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="0bf4ef8f-8061-49e1-a885-80a498157b48" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-287_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-288_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-290_">The lumbar spinal cord in the lower area of the back. Nerve roots coming from the spinal cord in the lumbar spine control the legs. The lumbar region is where the spinal cord ends (the spinal cord is shorter than the spine).</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-291_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-292_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="e1e88580-a498-457b-88f1-599ed6f8b3dc" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Which part of the spine is most vulnerable to injury?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="e1e88580-a498-457b-88f1-599ed6f8b3dc" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-294_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-295_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-297_">The lumbar spine contains 5 vertebral bones that form a lordotic curve (same as the cervical spine) and run through the lower back. The lumbar spine is more mobile than the thoracic spine yet also carries more weight, making it the most likely region of the spine to become injured and painful.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-298_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-299_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="7b48f159-9ed6-48b3-9cc7-2040568f7b17" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What happens if the spinal cord is removed?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="7b48f159-9ed6-48b3-9cc7-2040568f7b17" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-301_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-302_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-304_">When the spinal cord is damaged, the message from the brain cannot get through. The spinal nerves below the level of injury get signals, but they cannot go up the spinal tracts to the brain. Reflex movements can happen, but these are not movements that can be controlled.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-305_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-306_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="b3dcc720-4056-4f7b-979a-835362f9f0c6" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Is your spinal cord connected to your brain?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="b3dcc720-4056-4f7b-979a-835362f9f0c6" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-308_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-309_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-311_">At the base of the brain, the brain stem connects to the spinal cord and is made up of the midbrain, pons, and medulla oblongata.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-312_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-313_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="9862c4d8-503c-4cb5-9c7f-568748a23fb9" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Can spinal problems cause heart problems?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="9862c4d8-503c-4cb5-9c7f-568748a23fb9" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-315_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-316_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-318_">Patients with SCI have a higher risk of cardiovascular complications and long-term effects, as well as thromboembolism and autonomic dysreflexia.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-319_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-320_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="b59c7f56-8748-423f-b99e-9364ee39bd6c" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What part of the spine can paralyse you?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="b59c7f56-8748-423f-b99e-9364ee39bd6c" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-322_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-323_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-325_">Paralysis of the lower half of the body is called paraplegia. Paralysis below the neck, including both arms and legs, is called quadriplegia.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-326_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-327_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="3fb99e93-64ee-49bd-ac6c-2b3736baf466" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What are the two most easily injured portions of the spine?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="3fb99e93-64ee-49bd-ac6c-2b3736baf466" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-329_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-330_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-332_">The areas most prone to damage are cervical and lumbar portions. While the spine comprises multiple regions, the ones most susceptible to damage are the cervical and lumbar regions.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-333_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-334_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="bd6c6c2b-3736-4af4-a638-492c0d2ce229" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>How do I know if my back pain is severe?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="bd6c6c2b-3736-4af4-a638-492c0d2ce229" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-336_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-337_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-339_">Signs that it's time to call a doctor for your back pain:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-340_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-341_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-343_">You've been in pain for over a week.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-344_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-346_">Your pain extends to other body parts.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-347_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-349_">You have numbness, tingling or weakness.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-350_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-352_">You have pain after an accident.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-353_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-355_">Your pain is worse at certain times or in certain positions.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-356_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-358_">You're having problems with your bowels or urination.
</span></li></ul></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-359_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-360_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="ec2f3c28-47e2-4227-9e73-4e3f22cf3edd" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Can someone with spinal cord injury walk again?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="ec2f3c28-47e2-4227-9e73-4e3f22cf3edd" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-362_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-363_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-365_">Many factors play a role in regaining the ability to walk after a spinal cord injury. Fortunately, it is possible for many SCI survivors. There is potential to walk again after SCI because the spinal cord can reorganise itself and make adaptive neuroplasticity changes.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-366_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-367_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="2bc77fac-2bcf-40fb-9ea2-b2edb4ffb4dc" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Do you provide face to face training for human spine awareness?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="2bc77fac-2bcf-40fb-9ea2-b2edb4ffb4dc" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-369_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-370_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-372_">All our human spine training courses, packages, are delivered online. We do not provide any classroom or face-to-face training.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-373_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-374_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="fbdea2b2-edb4-4fb4-9c3e-00e882f8966f" data-active="false" data-pf-typ